When comparing these types of systems with our classes, we find that systems with only detectable super-Earths are 77% from Class II, 20% from Class I, and 3% from Class III. Systems with both super-Earths and cold Jupiters are 94% from Class III, with contributions from all others categories. We note that even a system of Class I is included here; this is because that system contains a rocky planet of 18 M⊕\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
